.TH "register_sound_special_device" 9 "register_sound_special_device" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
register_sound_special_device \- register a special sound node
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" register_sound_special_device
.BI "(const struct file_operations *fops "  ","
.BI "int unit "  ","
.BI "struct device *dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "fops" 12
File operations for the driver
.IP "unit" 12
Unit number to allocate
.IP "dev" 12
device pointer

Allocate a special sound device by minor number from the sound
subsystem.
.SH "RETURN"
The allocated number is returned on success. On failure,
a negative error code is returned.
